    <h2>The Tracking Problem Nobody Talks About</h2>

    <p>
      Knowing the target is one thing. Consistently hitting it is another. And this is where most men fall short — not from lack of willingness, but because the tools available for tracking nutrition were built for a different person entirely.
    </p>

    <p>
      Full calorie and macro tracking apps are powerful. They're also overwhelming, time-consuming, and almost universally abandoned within a week by men over 40 who just want to know one thing: <em>did I get enough protein today?</em>
    </p>

    <p>
      The complexity isn't a feature for this audience. It's the reason the habit doesn't stick.
    </p>

    <p>
One of the easiest ways to fix this is to spread your protein across the day using a simple system like the
<a href="/blog/30-gram-protein-rule/">30-gram rule</a>, instead of eating most of it at night.
</p>

